# Single ModelConfig (Gemini 2.5 Pro) for both planner and worker.
#
# Why Pro for both, not split Flash/Pro:
# Initial design split planner=Flash (cheap routing) and worker=Pro
# (prose). Flash on the planner kept emitting malformed function_calls
# (literal `print(f"...")` Python pseudo-code instead of a structured
# tool invocation to `worker`). Even with a single-target function_call
# shape (planner only ever calls worker), Flash's code-leakage pattern
# is unreliable for production tool routing.
#
# Pro 2.5 trade-offs accepted:
# - Higher per-token cost (~30× Flash at our POC scale = still <$50/mo)
# - Stochastic thought_signature emissions that occasionally close the
#   SSE without `final:true` — MITIGATED by the chat-frontend useChatStream
#   one-shot transparent retry (RETRYABLE_ERROR_PATTERNS).
#
# The cost-optimization that motivated the split (cheap classifier for
# hellos/off-topic) was not worth the function-call malformation risk
# that broke A2A delegation.
#
# A `model-planner` ModelConfig is no longer maintained in this skeleton.
# To re-split later (e.g. when Gemini 3 Flash ships with better
# function-call discipline), add a second ModelConfig CR below and point
# agent-planner.yaml.njk at it.
apiVersion: kagent.dev/v1alpha2
kind: ModelConfig
metadata:
  name: model
  namespace: agent-${{ values.agent_name }}
  annotations:
    argocd.argoproj.io/sync-wave: "1"
spec:
  provider: GeminiVertexAI
  model: gemini-2.5-pro
  apiKeySecret: kagent-vertex-credentials
  apiKeySecretKey: credentials.json
  geminiVertexAI:
    projectID: ${{ values.project_id }}
    location: us-central1
    # 16K accommodates verbose teaching prose (~500 words) + tables + the
    # inline plotly-json chart fence (charts are ~2-3K tokens each, up to
    # ~6K for scatter plots with many points). 4K was too tight and
    # truncated responses mid-chart-embed.
    maxOutputTokens: 16384
    temperature: "0"
